Plan: Client Code Refactoring & Bug Fixes
Here is the plan mapped out based on the transition to the Java WebSocket backend and the sanity-check auth model we discussed. We will strip the unearned client authority and fix the major visual and flow crashes.

Steps

Phase 1: Network & Protocol Fixes (Client-Server Alignment)

- Replace legacy Socket.io .emit calls with native WebSocket .send(JSON.stringify) payloads.
- Fix the "Doppelganger Bug" (rendering your own body locally) by fetching a valid id from the Java server's initial handshake instead of native WebSocket (which lacks an implicit ID).
- Implement Hybrid Damage Authority: Rip out local hit damage applications. The client will send a SHOOT packet containing target intent and weapon type. The Java backend will check basic validity (shooter ammo, target alive state, valid distance/angle vectors) and then broadcast DAMAGE / DEATH.


Phase 2: Game Flow & States Integration

Remove the forced 500ms transition hack running locally that bypasses multiplayer waiting rules.
Fix offline crashes by adding null-checks to multiplayer array lookups for offline compatibility.
Delegate Match Life-Cycle to server broadcasts (e.g., waiting for MATCH_START from the backend vs progressing locally).
Add state-teardown logic to clear orphaned window event bindings when switching states, preventing exponential memory leaks.
Remove global debug keys (like immediately forcing death states) and allow state machines to safely restart their current loops.


Phase 3: Visuals, Combat & UI Bugs

Fix Enemy Desync: Copy physics collider coordinates directly to the visual mesh.position during collision resolution so hitboxes don't visually separate from the meshes upon touching walls.
Fix weapon UI crashes: Remove direct DOM lookup functions (document.getElementById) as UI is natively canvas-based; port logic to the canvas HUD.
Stop spinning an infinite requestAnimationFrame loop internally when non-automatic weapons aren't actively firing.
Disable visual toggles on root UI instances when swapping menu tabs to prevent rendering text overlays blindly on top of each other.
(Low Priority) Add defensive object parsing in map loaders to prevent hardcrashes if an artist updates a model hierarchy slightly.


