Verification

Run a local client loop and verify that weapon shots send properly formatted JSON through WebSockets without generating TypeErrors.
Boot two simultaneous clients in multiplayer and ensure they wait indefinitely on the "Waiting" match screen until the server triggers the countdown/start phase.
Use Chrome Dev Tools Performance monitor to ensure switching in and out of the game repeatedly doesn't skyrocket event listener memory leaks.
Ram an enemy into a map boundary and ensure the model visual directly tracks with the invisible physics collider without freezing in place.


Decisions

Damage logic moved to a Hybrid "Sanity Check" validation design (Server does math validation on Client's hit claim).
Art logic/shaders intentionally bypassed in current review scope.
Hardcoded map dependencies added to list but deprioritized for initial prototype milestone.